              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 3",
              "title": "25m Canadian History: Grades 5-6 - Lesson 3",
              "body": "Joe and the Wreck of the Tribune\n⍞ Materials: Joe and the Wreck of the Tribune\n\n➜ RECAP\nWhat do you recall from last week's reading?\n\n➜ READ, NARRATE, & DISCUSS\np.24-35 \"Eli's derelict old shed\" - \"Nothing would burn today.\"\n• As you learn more about the characters, add to your list or chart.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recyw9Tjk8xQIKR3q&6J82c=recRDZBxwaT2WOKj4"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 4,
              "weekLabel": "Week 4",
              "sequence": 4,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 4",
              "title": "25m Canadian History: Grades 5-6 - Lesson 4",
              "body": "Joe and the Wreck of the Tribune\n⍞ Materials: Joe and the Wreck of the Tribune\n\n➜ RECAP\nWhat do you learn from last week's reading about Gram?\n\n➜ READ, NARRATE, & DISCUSS\np.36-47 \"Buttoned into his oilskins\" - \"mend a holey rowboat.\"\n• Earlier in the novel, we learned that Joe has never been to school. This was not unusual two hundred years ago, when children often needed to work inside or outside the home to help support their families. Why do you think Joe has never been to school? How does he learn what he needs to know? \n• Continue adding to your list of characters.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recyw9Tjk8xQIKR3q&6J82c=rec5svgiGhanU4ECs"
